# Identity Stabilization Diagrams
### ASCII Visualizations of Coherence, Continuity, Fragmentation, Integration, and Operator Dynamics

## 1. Identity Coherence Diagram
Coherence = alignment of identity layers.

Low Coherence:
Core:        [Self A]
Narrative:   [Self B]
Situational: [Self C]

ASCII:
[ A ]   [ B ]   [ C ]
 ^ misaligned layers

High Coherence:
Core:        [Self A]
Narrative:   [Self A]
Situational: [Self A]

ASCII:
[ A ]---[ A ]---[ A ]
 ^ aligned layers

---

## 2. Identity Continuity Diagram
Continuity = stable identity across time.

Discontinuity:
Past ----//---- Present ----//---- Future

ASCII:
[Past] --//-- [Now] --//-- [Future]
 ^ breaks in narrative

Continuity:
Past ----> Transition ----> Present ----> Transition ----> Future

ASCII:
[Past] ---> [Now] ---> [Future]
 ^ smooth temporal flow

---

## 3. Identity Fragmentation Diagram
Fragmentation = divergence of identity layers.

Horizontal Fragmentation:
Core:        [A]
Narrative:   [B]
Situational: [C]

ASCII:
[A]   |   [B]   |   [C]
 ^ layers contradict

Vertical Fragmentation:
Past:    [A]
Present: [B]
Future:  [C]

ASCII:
[A] ↓ [B] ↓ [C]
 ^ temporal identity breaks

Recursive Fragmentation:
Self → Self? → Self?? → Self???

ASCII:
[x] → [?] → [??] → [???]
 ^ recursive instability

---

## 4. Identity Integration Diagram
Integration = synthesis of identity layers.

Before Integration:
[A]   [B]   [C]

After Integration:
[A+B+C]

ASCII:
[A] + [B] + [C] ---> [ABC]
 ^ unified identity

Vertical Integration:
Past ↔ Present ↔ Future

ASCII:
[A] <--> [B] <--> [C]
 ^ temporal synthesis

Recursive Integration:
Self → Self' → Self'' → Meta-Self

ASCII:
[x] → [x'] → [x''] → [Meta-x]
 ^ recursive coherence

---

